                <fr:title text="Ideal of Jordan algebra">Ideal of Jordan algebra</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
                <fr:meta name="source">
                  <fr:link href="/baez-2002-octonions/" title="The Octonions" uri="http://localhost:8000/baez-2002-octonions/" display-uri="baez-2002-octonions" type="local">[baez-2002-octonions]</fr:link>
                </fr:meta>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>We define an <html:dfn>Ideal</html:dfn> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(J,\circ )]]></fr:tex> to be a subspace <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B\subseteq  J]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\circ  b\in  B]]></fr:tex> for every <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  J]]></fr:tex>. This generalizes the familiar notion of an ideal from rings (and things).</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
